      • getFormPopulationErrors

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getFormPopulationErrors()
        This map will contain any form population errors, such as trying to populate a numeric field with String values. The structure of the Map will be key=fieldName, value=validation message with the fieldName. Example "customInt1":"Abc is not a valid value for field: customInt1"
        Returns:
        Will return a map with any formPopulationErrors, key=fieldName, value=validation message with the fieldName.
